						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift made by the king of 497 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold and a gold flower weighing 2 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and odd to God Mahādēva at Tirumālpēṟu, when he paid a visit to the temple to offer worship. The present is said to have been conveyed by the officer Arumoḻi-Mūvēndavēḷāṉ of Kāraippākkam.</p>						

